ils such as a row of cups hanging on hooks and rattling away with the swaying of the train.<br /><br />Despite the fact that this film is widely acclaimed, I prefer <PERSON>Lars Von Trier</PERSON>'s later films (Breaking the Waves and The Idiots). The bomb scene described above really put me off. Perhaps I'm a realist.
