ion came about, his character seemed superfluous and the treatment he received mean-spirited. Were audiences supposed to laugh as he was abused? This seems to me that's what is implied and I don't like it at all.<br /><br />There are FAR better French films of the era (Le Million, <PERSON>La Femme du Boulanger</PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION>Fanny</ORGANIZATION>, Regain, and others) as well as better silent films. I just can't understand this film's high rating.
